Male body. Colour yellowish brown (in alcohol). Head with two prominent dorsolateral sulci, midcranial sulcus absent; anteromedian setal wart subtriangular, with one small, almost circular mediolateral setal wart at each posterior corner; oblong dorsolateral setal warts following eye margin, almost merging with posterolateral setal warts (
Fig. 1
